subSubSection.paragraph:
Colour
. The dorsal carapace surface of fresh 

O. dehaani

is grey to dark purplish-brown, often with black or dark blotches on the gastric and adjacent areas (
Fig. 53A, C
). The chelipeds vary from white to pale purple (see also 
Miyake, 1983
; 
Minemizu, 2000
; 
Liu & Wang, 2010
; 
Li & Chiu, 2013
; 
Toyota & Seki, 2014
).
